I poked her all night.

59
00:06:02,105 --> 00:06:04,335
A toast, I say a toast.

60
00:06:05,185 --> 00:06:07,983
To Queen Catherine.
Who doesn't give a fig.

61
00:06:08,185 --> 00:06:10,335
- God bless her.
- To the queen of England!

62
00:06:16,825 --> 00:06:19,783
His Majesty, the king.

63
00:06:34,385 --> 00:06:36,899
- My lords.
- Your Majesty.

64
00:06:44,665 --> 00:06:46,417
You look splendid.

65
00:06:53,985 --> 00:06:57,978
So my sources have just told me
that the emperor believes...

66
00:06:58,185 --> 00:07:01,177
...Wolsey is to blame
for instigating the divorce.

67
00:07:01,385 --> 00:07:04,741
He believes that the people of England
will soon rise up...

68
00:07:04,945 --> 00:07:06,981
...and bring that creature
to the scaffold.

69
00:07:07,185 --> 00:07:09,301
His end is surely approaching.

70
00:07:09,505 --> 00:07:13,259
After which, Your Grace
will be the first man at court.

71
00:07:13,745 --> 00:07:14,814
As you ought to be.

72
00:07:15,025 --> 00:07:16,617
In which case, Boleyn...

73
00:07:16,825 --> 00:07:20,181
...I shall not fail to promote
your family's interests.

74
00:07:20,385 --> 00:07:25,459
It's true you have risen high.
But you shall rise higher yet.

75
00:07:30,145 --> 00:07:33,137
Did you see?
They were all looking at you.

76
00:07:34,665 --> 00:07:37,941
I'm glad. I want them to look at you.

77
00:07:38,145 --> 00:07:40,943
I want them to be envious.

78
00:07:43,065 --> 00:07:47,422
I want all of them to know
exactly how much I love you.

79
00:07:48,585 --> 00:07:52,658
Then like my family motto,
I am "the most happy."

80
00:07:57,865 --> 00:08:02,097
- How did it go in court today?
- Well enough.

81
00:08:02,345 --> 00:08:04,222
Yet Catherine refuses to attend.

82
00:08:05,305 --> 00:08:07,182
It will make no difference.

83
00:08:07,385 --> 00:08:09,819
Wolsey promises me
I will have a divorce by summer.

84
00:08:10,945 --> 00:08:12,139
Promises are easy.

85
00:08:15,785 --> 00:08:17,343
What if you don't?

86
00:08:30,025 --> 00:08:31,583
Margaret, what is it?

87
00:08:35,265 --> 00:08:36,664
I couldn't sleep.

88
00:08:37,425 --> 00:08:39,381
Come back to bed. It's cold.

89
00:08:39,985 --> 00:08:41,338
Not yet.

90
00:08:44,025 --> 00:08:47,256
I'm going to court tomorrow.
Will you come?

91
00:08:47,505 --> 00:08:50,303
Your brother has asked again
for your presence.

92
00:08:50,865 --> 00:08:52,856
I told you.

93
00:08:53,065 --> 00:08:58,378
Not while he makes love in public
to that Boleyn girl.

94
00:09:00,665 --> 00:09:03,737
It's offensive
and it makes him look like a fool.

95
00:09:05,505 --> 00:09:09,498
Everyone else can see how proud
and grasping the Boleyns are.

96
00:09:09,705 --> 00:09:13,937
- Why can't he?
- What if he commands you to come?

97
00:09:32,185 --> 00:09:33,937
What is this?

98
00:09:35,745 --> 00:09:39,340
Only a wife to a husband.

99
00:09:43,545 --> 00:09:47,823
Sleep now, my sweet Charles.

100
00:09:52,265 --> 00:09:54,381
I pray you, sleep.

101
00:10:47,225 --> 00:10:49,819
Silence in the court.

102
00:10:52,585 --> 00:10:57,261
In the absence of the queen,
we have been asked by her council...

103
00:10:57,465 --> 00:11:01,936
...Bishop Fisher,
to make a statement to this court.

104
00:11:02,145 --> 00:11:04,101
And being the circumstances...

105
00:11:04,305 --> 00:11:09,379
...we have decided
that such a statement is admissible.

106
00:11:09,905 --> 00:11:11,304
Your Grace.

107
00:11:18,465 --> 00:11:22,822
Your Honours,
you have been asked to give verdict...

108
00:11:23,025 --> 00:11:25,937
...on the validity
of the royal marriage.

109
00:11:26,425 --> 00:11:32,261
Sirs, it is my contention that
this marriage of the king and queen...

110
00:11:32,465 --> 00:11:38,176
...can be dissolved by no power,
human or divine.

111
00:11:39,705 --> 00:11:44,062
Let me give, if I might,
a Biblical parallel.

112
00:11:44,265 --> 00:11:48,975
You will remember, I am sure,
the tyrant Herod Antipas.

113
00:11:49,905 --> 00:11:52,499
Who disembarrassed himself
of his wife.

114
00:11:52,745 --> 00:11:56,055
In order that he might take
his brother's wife.

115
00:11:56,265 --> 00:11:57,300
Damn you.

116
00:11:57,505 --> 00:12:01,180
And who then executed
John the Baptist...

117
00:12:01,425 --> 00:12:05,304
...when he dared to criticize
the royal couple.

118
00:12:05,865 --> 00:12:10,416
Just as John the Baptist,
so I, in all humility...

119
00:12:10,625 --> 00:12:15,858
...say to you here today
that I am ready to lay down my life.

120
00:12:16,065 --> 00:12:17,544
To lay down my life...

121
00:12:17,745 --> 00:12:22,421
...to defend the sanctity of marriage
and to condemn adultery.

122
00:12:23,065 --> 00:12:24,737
Outrageous.

123
00:12:25,265 --> 00:12:27,017
Your Honours.

124
00:12:27,545 --> 00:12:30,582
I accuse this man, Bishop Fisher...

125
00:12:30,825 --> 00:12:35,580
...of arrogance, temerity
and disloyalty.

126
00:12:36,585 --> 00:12:41,613
I demand that you disregard
every vile word.

127
00:12:50,185 --> 00:12:51,300
Thomas. Come in.

128
00:12:51,505 --> 00:12:54,417
- Drink?
- Not for me, thank you.

129
00:12:54,625 --> 00:12:56,024
No.

130
00:12:58,825 --> 00:13:01,385
I have a mission for you, Thomas.

131
00:13:02,785 --> 00:13:06,539
The French and lmperial forces
have ceased their aggression.

132
00:13:06,745 --> 00:13:10,738
There is to be some sort of conference
at a place called Cambria, in France...

133
00:13:10,945 --> 00:13:15,655
...between their negotiators and also
with representatives of the pope.

134
00:13:16,585 --> 00:13:19,782
I, of course, am unable to attend.

135
00:13:19,985 --> 00:13:22,374
Now the vital thing, Thomas...

136
00:13:23,465 --> 00:13:27,140
...is that there be no agreement
between the other two parties.

137
00:13:27,345 --> 00:13:30,178
I have had private reassurances
from the king of France...

138
00:13:30,385 --> 00:13:32,501
Who is, after all, our ally.

139
00:13:32,705 --> 00:13:37,221
- That he will never make peace with
the emperor, under any circumstances.

140
00:13:37,465 --> 00:13:40,298
Similarly, there must there be
no rapprochement...

141
00:13:40,505 --> 00:13:43,542
...between the Holy Father
and the emperor.

142
00:13:43,745 --> 00:13:45,895
You must understand
under those circumstances...

143
00:13:46,105 --> 00:13:49,939
...it would be impossible for the pope
to grant the king his desire.

144
00:13:50,505 --> 00:13:53,497
- Yes, I do understand.
- Now...

145
00:13:55,745 --> 00:13:59,294
You have your principles,
I understand that.

146
00:13:59,505 --> 00:14:02,338
But for the love we both have
for the king...

147
00:14:02,545 --> 00:14:06,094
...your job at Cambria
is to be as obstructive as possible.

148
00:14:06,545 --> 00:14:09,013
Don't let Francis renege
on his commitments to us.

149
00:14:09,225 --> 00:14:12,058
And don't let the pope forget
that it was Charles' forces...

150
00:14:12,265 --> 00:14:14,574
...that invaded and sacked Rome.

151
00:14:16,865 --> 00:14:18,901
And there is one other thing.

152
00:14:19,305 --> 00:14:20,533
More than this?

153
00:14:20,785 --> 00:14:24,061
Try to discover, by subtle means,
through his agents...

154
00:14:24,265 --> 00:14:28,497
...if the emperor is prepared
to support his aunt by use of force.

155
00:14:28,745 --> 00:14:31,543
You think he might invade England
in support of the queen?

156
00:14:31,785 --> 00:14:36,381
I don't think anything.
But I imagine everything.

157
00:14:37,025 --> 00:14:40,381
And it is those imaginings
that cause me great pain, Thomas.

158
00:14:41,065 --> 00:14:42,657
Great pain.

159
00:14:43,785 --> 00:14:46,094
But then wasn't it you that said:

160
00:14:46,305 --> 00:14:50,423
"No man can expect to go to heaven
on a feather bed."

161
00:15:07,865 --> 00:15:09,742
Have you no kind things to say?

162
00:15:10,985 --> 00:15:13,499
- Kind?
- To your wife.

163
00:15:13,745 --> 00:15:16,339
The mother of your child.

164
00:15:16,545 --> 00:15:19,423
You treat me so unkindly.
And in public, neglect me.

165
00:15:19,665 --> 00:15:22,338
Catherine,
you must accept the inevitable.

166
00:15:22,545 --> 00:15:25,139
The weight of academic opinion
is against us.

167
00:15:25,385 --> 00:15:29,822
We were never legally man and wife.
And the court will decide in my favour.

168
00:15:30,065 --> 00:15:32,215
And if the court does not decide
in my favour...

169
00:15:32,465 --> 00:15:36,424
...I shall denounce the pope as
a heretic and marry whom I please.

170
00:15:42,985 --> 00:15:44,418
Sweetheart.

171
00:15:47,785 --> 00:15:51,300
By all the angels,
I was intact when I came to your bed.

172
00:15:51,545 --> 00:15:53,934
All right.
So you were a fucking virgin!

173
00:15:54,145 --> 00:15:56,101
That's not the point.

174
00:16:06,705 --> 00:16:10,095
Did I not tell you that if you argued
with her she'd have the upper hand?

175
00:16:10,305 --> 00:16:13,854
I see now, one morning you'll succumb
to her reasoning and cast me off!

176
00:16:14,065 --> 00:16:15,862
What do you mean?

177
00:16:16,465 --> 00:16:20,856
- Anne, I love you.
- Let me go, let me go.

178
00:16:21,985 --> 00:16:24,783
Why don't you see?
Why can't you understand?

179
00:16:24,985 --> 00:16:28,216
I've been waiting for so long.
For what?

180
00:16:28,745 --> 00:16:31,213
