some advantageous marriage...

181
00:16:31,465 --> 00:16:35,174
...and borne sons which is a woman's
greatest consolation in this life.

182
00:16:35,385 --> 00:16:38,616
Instead, I've been wasting my time
and my youth. For no purpose at all.

183
00:16:38,825 --> 00:16:41,100
Anne, stop this.

184
00:16:41,305 --> 00:16:44,024
You will have sons.
We will have sons.

185
00:16:44,265 --> 00:16:46,779
No, no. It's too late.

186
00:16:47,025 --> 00:16:49,903
Your wife won't let you go.
I should have realized.

187
00:16:50,105 --> 00:16:51,663
- Where are you going?
- Home.

188
00:16:51,865 --> 00:16:54,140
Stay here, I beg you. Anne.

189
00:16:54,345 --> 00:16:56,984
I'm the king of England!

190
00:16:57,545 --> 00:17:01,254
Make way for His Grace. Make way.

191
00:17:10,625 --> 00:17:12,138
Your Eminence.

192
00:17:16,665 --> 00:17:20,340
- An urgent message from the pope.
- Thank you, kind sir.

193
00:17:31,665 --> 00:17:33,974
Look.
He is always leaning on someone.

194
00:17:35,185 --> 00:17:38,018
Perhaps
someone should lean on him.

195
00:17:38,225 --> 00:17:40,136
Perhaps.

196
00:17:42,145 --> 00:17:44,295
- Your Eminence.
- Your Majesty.

197
00:17:45,625 --> 00:17:49,857
- I trust we will soon have a verdict.
- Indeed.

198
00:17:57,065 --> 00:17:59,374
We hear with great distress
of events in Germany.

199
00:17:59,625 --> 00:18:03,937
- The destruction of the churches.
- Melancholy events, Majesty.

200
00:18:04,425 --> 00:18:06,381
But why is it happening?

201
00:18:07,225 --> 00:18:08,499
Majesty?

202
00:18:09,185 --> 00:18:11,016
I'll tell you.

203
00:18:11,865 --> 00:18:14,743
The Lutherans attack what they see
as the wickedness of Rome.

204
00:18:15,705 --> 00:18:17,935
They believe
corruption is rewarded...

205
00:18:18,185 --> 00:18:23,134
...but the faithful are abandoned
and badly treated.

206
00:18:27,265 --> 00:18:30,177
I am a man of faith, Your Eminence.

207
00:18:32,865 --> 00:18:35,777
God forbid His Holiness
should ever turn his back on me.

208
00:19:18,465 --> 00:19:21,218
Alas, my love, you do me wrong

209
00:19:21,425 --> 00:19:25,862
To treat me so discourteously

210
00:19:27,345 --> 00:19:29,222
Don't you ever get tired of it,
Charles?

211
00:19:29,425 --> 00:19:31,541
Of course. Then I go to sleep.

212
00:19:31,745 --> 00:19:33,940
I bet you dream of women too.

213
00:19:34,185 --> 00:19:38,736
No, I dream of God.
Of heaven and hell and of repentance.

214
00:19:39,825 --> 00:19:41,417
Since you asked.

215
00:19:49,185 --> 00:19:51,380
What are you thinking, Anthony?

216
00:19:51,585 --> 00:19:56,739
I'm listening to that song,
and I'm thinking, omnia vincit amor.

217
00:20:02,345 --> 00:20:03,858
No one can resist love.

218
00:20:16,705 --> 00:20:19,936
- My lord.
- Your Majesty.

219
00:20:22,345 --> 00:20:27,100
Please ask Anne to come back to court.
I beg you for my sake.

220
00:20:27,305 --> 00:20:29,261
I can't live without her.

221
00:20:29,785 --> 00:20:34,256
Tomorrow I shall have my verdict
and I shall be free.

222
00:20:36,225 --> 00:20:37,817
Majesty.

223
00:21:01,105 --> 00:21:05,940
Eminences, in accordance with
the rules and laws of this tribunal...

224
00:21:06,145 --> 00:21:07,817
...and the wishes of His Majesty.

225
00:21:08,025 --> 00:21:11,301
I ask you officially
to deliver your judgement.

226
00:21:16,305 --> 00:21:19,456
Your Majesty, my lords.

227
00:21:19,665 --> 00:21:22,179
After much deliberation,
we have decided...

228
00:21:22,385 --> 00:21:26,219
...that this great matter is too important
to be here decided...

229
00:21:26,425 --> 00:21:30,543
...without consultation
with the curia at Rome.

230
00:21:30,745 --> 00:21:35,421
Unfortunately,
the curia is now in summer recess.

231
00:21:35,625 --> 00:21:38,776
In which case,
there is no alternative...

232
00:21:38,985 --> 00:21:44,935
...but to prorogue this tribunal
until October 1 st.

233
00:21:45,145 --> 00:21:47,295
That is our judgement.

234
00:22:35,865 --> 00:22:38,777
You stupid cunt.

235
00:22:45,945 --> 00:22:49,381
