a head on your shoulders.

240
00:23:11,305 --> 00:23:12,294
Happy day.

241
00:23:12,585 --> 00:23:13,859
Indeed, Senor Mendoza.

242
00:23:18,425 --> 00:23:21,417
Campeggio received secret
instructions from His Holiness...

243
00:23:21,625 --> 00:23:24,264
...who has advocated the matter
back to Rome.

244
00:23:24,905 --> 00:23:26,099
I was not abandoned.

245
00:23:26,305 --> 00:23:29,058
The emperor worked tirelessly
for your cause.

246
00:23:33,865 --> 00:23:35,662
It is true you are leaving?

247
00:23:36,745 --> 00:23:38,576
Yes, Your Majesty.

248
00:23:39,705 --> 00:23:41,821
Ambassador Chapuys
will replace me.

249
00:23:43,625 --> 00:23:45,217
I know him.

250
00:23:46,065 --> 00:23:47,703
He's a most trustworthy person...

251
00:23:47,945 --> 00:23:50,778
...and will take up your defence
with fidelity and diligence.

252
00:23:50,985 --> 00:23:54,261
As you have done, Senor Mendoza.

253
00:24:03,185 --> 00:24:05,221
In memory of me.

254
00:24:16,065 --> 00:24:17,339
Majesty.

255
00:24:32,225 --> 00:24:36,662
Thomas, how very good to see you.
How is the king?

256
00:24:37,545 --> 00:24:43,063
The king is going on a progress.
Immediately.

257
00:24:43,585 --> 00:24:46,099
With the Lady Anne.

258
00:24:46,305 --> 00:24:47,704
I see.

259
00:24:48,505 --> 00:24:51,815
Tell His Majesty that I am
handing over to him at once...

260
00:24:52,025 --> 00:24:54,141
...the entire revenues
of the see of Durham.

261
00:24:54,345 --> 00:24:55,983
It is one of the richest in England.

262
00:24:56,185 --> 00:25:00,861
And tell him I shall not cease to work
for his great matter.

263
00:25:01,065 --> 00:25:06,139
Campeggio and I will gladly accomplish
his lawful desire. Do you see?

264
00:25:07,025 --> 00:25:09,858
- I shall tell him.
- And Thomas...

265
00:25:13,905 --> 00:25:19,855
Tell me I can trust you
to advocate my interests to the king.

266
00:25:22,025 --> 00:25:23,663
You may.

267
00:25:24,265 --> 00:25:29,180
For without you, I would be
a lowly clerk, without profit or future.

268
00:25:29,785 --> 00:25:31,741
I owe you my life.

269
00:25:54,905 --> 00:25:56,304
I've been summoned to Rome.

270
00:25:56,505 --> 00:25:59,065
I have to appear before the pope
and answer for myself.

271
00:25:59,265 --> 00:26:00,334
Can you imagine it?

272
00:26:00,545 --> 00:26:05,539
Me, the king of England,
who answers to no authority, but God!

273
00:26:05,745 --> 00:26:09,135
Damn Wolsey. Damn him to hell.

274
00:26:09,385 --> 00:26:12,775
- May I speak plainly?
- Yes, of course.

275
00:26:13,625 --> 00:26:16,776
There are some who on good authority
care not for popes.

276
00:26:17,505 --> 00:26:19,780
These writers say that the king...

277
00:26:19,985 --> 00:26:23,944
...is both emperor and pope
absolutely in his own kingdom.

278
00:26:24,465 --> 00:26:25,978
Which writers?

279
00:26:27,545 --> 00:26:31,458
I have a book to show you,
with your permission?

280
00:26:35,265 --> 00:26:37,017
Show it to me.

281
00:28:22,985 --> 00:28:26,421
Softly love and to love softly.

282
00:28:26,905 --> 00:28:29,021
Dew on the sycamore branch.

283
00:28:29,225 --> 00:28:33,264
By the creaking gate.
Where my heart hurries afterwards.

284
00:28:33,465 --> 00:28:38,539
Through the path of wheat,
along the briar, to that stone.

285
00:28:38,745 --> 00:28:40,975
Under which I lie.

286
00:29:08,385 --> 00:29:10,694
- Thank you for the audience.
- Very well, my lords.

287
00:29:10,905 --> 00:29:13,624
- Your Majesty.
- Majesty.

288
00:29:13,865 --> 00:29:15,218
Lord Rochford?

289
00:29:15,425 --> 00:29:18,019
Majesty, the new lmperial Ambassador,
Mr. Chapuys...

290
00:29:18,225 --> 00:29:21,183
...asks permission to present
his credentials to the queen.

291
00:29:21,385 --> 00:29:24,741
Granted.
My lord, is there anything else?

292
00:29:25,385 --> 00:29:28,183
Your Majesty, Cardinal Campeggio
is returning to Rome...

293
00:29:28,385 --> 00:29:31,616
...and would like to take
his formal leave of Your Majesty.

294
00:29:33,145 --> 00:29:34,863
Very well.

295
00:29:35,065 --> 00:29:38,819
Mr. Cromwell,
invite him here to Grafton House.

296
00:29:39,065 --> 00:29:42,978
Also Wolsey. Anything else?

297
00:29:51,505 --> 00:29:52,699
Your Grace?

298
00:29:54,065 --> 00:29:56,101
Majesty, forgive me.

299
00:30:06,625 --> 00:30:08,377
Margaret is dead.

300
00:30:12,985 --> 00:30:14,703
She died of consumption.

301
00:30:38,185 --> 00:30:40,858
You never even told me
she was sick.

302
00:31:32,705 --> 00:31:35,902
If that's the king's sister,
why isn't the king here?

303
00:31:36,105 --> 00:31:38,414
- The king cannot go to funerals.
- Why?

304
00:31:38,625 --> 00:31:40,934
No one is allowed
to imagine the death of the king.

305
00:31:41,145 --> 00:31:42,897
For that would be treason.

306
00:32:42,105 --> 00:32:43,584
Forgive me.

307
00:32:47,465 --> 00:32:49,103
I'm sorry.

308
00:32:58,185 --> 00:33:01,461
Come, come, Thomas.
Tell me what happened.

309
00:33:01,705 --> 00:33:04,538
I take it you arrived at Cambria
on time?

310
00:33:04,745 --> 00:33:08,181
Not exactly. We were a week late.

311
00:33:09,105 --> 00:33:10,697
A week?

312
00:33:11,425 --> 00:33:14,417
Then how could you have contributed
to the substantive arguments?

313
00:33:14,665 --> 00:33:18,101
No, we couldn't. We weren't privy
to the main discussions.

314
00:33:18,625 --> 00:33:22,664
We were only able to enter into
negotiations with the major parties.

315
00:33:22,905 --> 00:33:24,577
What negotiations?

316
00:33:24,785 --> 00:33:27,253
Well, I'm happy to report
that we secured a return...

317
00:33:27,465 --> 00:33:29,501
...to mutually beneficial
trade relations...

318
00:33:29,705 --> 00:33:31,616
...between ourselves
and the Low Countries.

319
00:33:31,825 --> 00:33:34,703
We also obtained guarantees
regarding long-standing payments...

320
00:33:34,905 --> 00:33:36,577
...owing to the king by the emperor.

321
00:33:37,225 --> 00:33:39,580
But the major disputes, Thomas.
The major disputes!

322
00:33:39,785 --> 00:33:44,017
What happened? Did the king
of France refuse to make peace?

323
00:33:44,225 --> 00:33:45,453
No.

324
00:33:46,225 --> 00:33:51,219
No, on the contrary, he settled
all his differences with the emperor.

325
00:33:52,545 --> 00:33:56,504
Both of them settled their differences
with His Holiness Pope Clement.

326
00:33:57,345 --> 00:33:59,859
In other words,
we were deliberately sidelined.

327
00:34:00,865 --> 00:34:02,583
If you choose to put it like that.

328
00:34:17,145 --> 00:34:21,457
Now there is no chance that the pope
will give the king his divorce.

329
00:34:26,065 --> 00:34:27,578
Tell me, Thomas.

330
00:34:29,585 --> 00:34:32,657
What exactly do you think
you might have achieved at Cambria...

331
00:34:32,865 --> 00:34:35,538
...that makes you look so smug?

332
00:34:38,425 --> 00:34:39,858
With respect, Your Eminence...

333
00:34:40,065 --> 00:34:42,533
...to some degree
it wasn't for me to achieve anything.

334
00:34:44,305 --> 00:34:47,422
Yet I consider this diplomacy
to be somewhat successful.

335
00:34:47,665 --> 00:34:50,225
Once more, there is peace in Europe.

336
00:34:51,545 --> 00:34:53,536
England is at peace with the empire.

337
00:34:54,185 --> 00:34:58,656
More importantly, papal authority
is restored and recognized.

338
00:34:59,265 --> 00:35:01,176
That is what I believe in.

339
00:35:03,065 --> 00:35:06,978
- Francis betrayed me.
- Francis saw the futility of war.

340
00:35:08,345 --> 00:35:11,098
He recognized the need for tradition.

341
00:35:12,265 --> 00:35:14,699
And you, Thomas...

342
00:35:17,665 --> 00:35:19,974
...you have destroyed me.

343
00:35:37,105 --> 00:35:39,255
Make way.

344
00:35:59,745 --> 00:36:02,054
This way, Your Excellency.

345
00:36:20,945 --> 00:36:23,175
Your Honour's chamber.

346
00:36:23,945 --> 00:36:25,298
Thank you.

347
00:36:35,585 --> 00:36:38,258
Wait. Wait.

348
00:36:39,785 --> 00:36:41,013
Where is my chamber?

349
00:36:41,265 --> 00:36:43,574
There is none prepared for you,
Your Eminence.

350
00:36:46,265 --> 00:36:48,096
I must change
from my riding clothes.

351
00:36:48,705 --> 00:36:51,219
Then you had best ask elsewhere.

352
00:37:06,785 --> 00:37:08,423
Your Eminence.

353
00:37:10,065 --> 00:37:12,977
- Mr. Norris.
- Use my room.

354
00:37:13,185 --> 00:37:15,255
It's not much, but...

355
00:37:15,465 --> 00:37:18,104
I'll have your trunk sent up.

356
00:37:18,865 --> 00:37:21,902
When you've changed,
you are to go to the presence chamber.

357
00:37:23,345 --> 00:37:24,937
I am very grateful to you, Norris.

358
00:37:25,145 --> 00:37:29,104
There are many here, sir,
who have cause to be grateful to you.

359
00:37:29,305 --> 00:37:31,944
Though alas, they do not show it.

360
00:37:48,065 --> 00:37:51,182
Cardinals Wolsey and Campeggio.

361
00:38:20,985 --> 00:38:24,341
I hear you have been unwell.
Is it true?

362
00:38:25,825 --> 00:38:29,738
Majesty, when was I ever
unwell enough not to serve you?

363
00:38:30,585 --> 00:38:34,817
That's what I thought.
They tell such lies, these people.

364
00:38:40,425 --> 00:38:42,416
Who can I trust?

365
00:38:45,145 --> 00:38:48,137
We've come a long way together,
you and I, cardinal.

366
00:38:48,625 --> 00:38:50,058
Did you think I'd forget?

367
00:38:50,265 --> 00:38:53,257
And there is still
a great deal more to do.

368
00:38:53,465 --> 00:38:54,693
I know, I know.

369
00:39:00,025 --> 00:39:02,061
Don't be afraid.

370
00:39:03,865 --> 00:39:06,425
We shall talk properly tomorrow.

371
00:39:48,625 --> 00:39:50,661
Good morning, sweetheart.

372
00:39:52,785 --> 00:39:54,138
Halt!

373
00:39:54,345 --> 00:39:56,779
Stand aside,
I must speak with the king.

374
00:39:57,705 --> 00:39:58,899
Stand aside.

375
00:40:01,345 --> 00:40:03,097
Your Majesty.

376
00:40:04,105 --> 00:40:07,495
Majesty! Your Majesty!

377
00:40:07,745 --> 00:40:09,815
Majesty!

378
00:40:10,705 --> 00:40:12,263
Majesty!

379
00:40:13,345 --> 00:40:15,700
Majesty!

380
00:40:18,025 --> 00:40:20,255
Ambassador Chapuys.

381
00:40:20,745 --> 00:40:22,576
Your Majesty.

382
00:40:23,865 --> 00:40:25,696
I have come at the king's invitation...

383
00:40:25,905 --> 00:40:29,136
...to present my credentials
from the emperor.

384
00:40:30,385 --> 00:40:31,704
Please.

385
00:40:38,105 --> 00:40:40,221
I am glad to see you.

386
00:40:40,425 --> 00:40:43,178
You know your mission has fallen
at a complicated time.

387
00:40:43,425 --> 00:40:48,340
Indeed. I see my mission, madame,
as one of toute douceur.

388
00:40:49,705 --> 00:40:51,377
All sweetness.

389
00:40:52,185 --> 00:40:54,824
May I ask Your Highness
if I should now, at once...

390
00:40:55,025 --> 00:40:58,734
...also present my credentials
to His Eminence, Cardinal Wolsey?

391
00:41:00,385 --> 00:41:03,775
I do not see
that there is such a need as before.

392
00:41:03,985 --> 00:41:07,819
The cardinal is somewhat undone.

393
00:41:08,025 --> 00:41:11,222
He has been refused permission
to attend court.

394
00:41:15,185 --> 00:41:20,179
- Then who should I attend instead?
- Norfolk, Suffolk and Rochford.

395
00:41:20,945 --> 00:41:24,335
They are now closest to the king,
and carry out his affairs.

396
00:41:24,545 --> 00:41:27,139
Seek them out,
if you would know things.

397
00:41:28,425 --> 00:41:31,940
You should also know, ambassador,
that they are not great friends of mine.

398
00:41:32,145 --> 00:41:33,624
Any of them.

399
00:41:34,265 --> 00:41:38,656
In fact, better to say,
they are all my mortal enemies.

400
00:41:43,385 --> 00:41:44,943
Make way.

401
00:41:59,025 --> 00:42:04,657
Cardinal Wolsey,
you are here charged with praemunire.

402
00:42:04,905 --> 00:42:08,944
That is exercising your powers
of papal legate in the king's realm.

403
00:42:09,185 --> 00:42:11,904
Thus derogating
the king's lawful authority.

404
00:42:12,145 --> 00:42:14,101
You are to be dismissed
of all your offices.

405
00:42:14,305 --> 00:42:16,739
And all your goods shall be taken
to the king's hands.

406
00:42:18,705 --> 00:42:21,299
I take it you have the king's
written authority for this?

407
00:42:30,865 --> 00:42:35,893
You are commanded to relinquish
the great seal of your office.

408
00:42:39,545 --> 00:42:42,423
- And where am I to go?
- To the king's house at Jericho.

409
00:42:43,705 --> 00:42:46,458
To await the verdict of the court.

410
00:42:59,425 --> 00:43:03,543
Make way for His Lord's Grace there.

411
00:43:10,145 --> 00:43:13,581
How about a blessing now,
Your Eminence?

412
00:43:18,625 --> 00:43:21,856
My own eternally beloved Cromwell.

413
00:43:22,065 --> 00:43:26,741
I beseech you, as you love me
and will ever do anything for me...

414
00:43:26,945 --> 00:43:30,255
...come here today,
as soon as your work is finished...

415
00:43:30,465 --> 00:43:32,342
...and forgetting everything else.

416
00:43:32,545 --> 00:43:37,141
I would not only communicate things
to you for my own comfort and relief...

417
00:43:37,345 --> 00:43:43,341
...but would also have your good, sad,
discreet advice and counsel.

418
00:43:43,585 --> 00:43:46,543
In haste, this Saturday...

419
00:43:46,745 --> 00:43:52,263
...with the rude hand and sorrowful
heart of your assured who loves you.

420
00:43:52,465 --> 00:43:54,057
Wolsey.

421
00:44:11,625 --> 00:44:14,344
Wolsey pleaded guilty
to all the charges made against him.

422
00:44:14,545 --> 00:44:17,855
Yes, I heard.
And sentenced to prison.

423
00:44:18,065 --> 00:44:19,942
I have rescinded his punishment.

424
00:44:20,145 --> 00:44:23,217
I've even agreed
to let him keep the Bishopric of York.

425
00:44:23,425 --> 00:44:26,064
With a pension of 3000 angels.

426
00:44:27,865 --> 00:44:30,299
You see what kind of monster I am?

427
00:44:33,065 --> 00:44:37,263
I need to appoint a new chancellor.
Someone I can trust.

428
00:44:37,785 --> 00:44:40,618
You're trained as a lawyer
and in royal service.

429
00:44:41,305 --> 00:44:43,739
You have international prestige.

430
00:44:43,945 --> 00:44:48,814
The friend of Erasmus,
the greatest humanist in all England.

431
00:44:49,225 --> 00:44:51,978
- You have a fine, sharp mind.
- No.

432
00:44:52,185 --> 00:44:54,540
- No what?
- No, I don't want to be Chancellor.

433
00:44:54,785 --> 00:44:57,458
You will do as I command!

434
00:45:05,625 --> 00:45:09,937
Listen, Thomas. I know you have
scruples concerning my divorce.

435
00:45:10,185 --> 00:45:12,745
And I swear to you,
it will only be dealt with...

436
00:45:12,945 --> 00:45:15,584
...by those whose consciences
agree with it.

437
00:45:15,785 --> 00:45:17,821
I'll only use you for other things...

438
00:45:18,025 --> 00:45:20,823
...and I will never let it
molest your conscience.

439
00:45:24,065 --> 00:45:26,625
Look, Tom.

440
00:45:28,625 --> 00:45:34,780
I want you, nay, I command you,
in all the things that you do...

441
00:45:34,985 --> 00:45:39,536
...to look to God first,
and only then to me.

